================================================================================
Third-party attributions
================================================================================

This product includes work derived from Aider — an AI pair-programming tool by
Aider-AI:

  https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider

Specifically, the tree-sitter tag query files under
`bin/_lib/repo-map-grammars/queries/*.scm` are lifted verbatim from Aider's
`aider/queries/tree-sitter-*-tags.scm` files. They are used here in support of
Orchestray's repo-map feature (R-AIDER-FULL, shipped in v2.1.17).

Aider is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0:

  http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

The six query files (bash.scm, go.scm, javascript.scm, python.scm, rust.scm,
typescript.scm) each carry an in-file header comment naming the upstream Aider
source path and the Apache-2.0 license. Their content is unmodified from Aider.
The surrounding repo-map implementation (graph construction, PageRank ranking,
cache, render, and grammar loader) is original Orchestray work under MIT.

================================================================================
Bundled WebAssembly grammars
================================================================================

The six tree-sitter grammar binaries under `bin/_lib/repo-map-grammars/` are
compiled WebAssembly distributions of the corresponding upstream tree-sitter
language repositories. Each grammar is licensed under MIT or a permissive MIT-
compatible license; consult the upstream repositories for verbatim license
text:

  - tree-sitter-bash         https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-bash
  - tree-sitter-go           https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-go
  - tree-sitter-javascript   https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-javascript
  - tree-sitter-python       https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-python
  - tree-sitter-rust         https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-rust
  - tree-sitter-typescript   https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-typescript
